            "annotations": [
                {
                    "id": "https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00321/canvas/1/page/p1",
                    "type": "AnnotationPage",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "id": "https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00321/canvas/1/4980dea8-2a58-4fc4-a218-1106d15e89e1",
                            "type": "Annotation",
                            "motivation": "commenting",
                            "body": [
                                {
                                    "created": "2025-07-29T20:32:34.924Z",
                                    "creator": "Naveah",
                                    "purpose": "commenting",
                                    "type": "TextualBody",
                                    "format": "text/html",
                                    "value": "<p>The background shows a divide between&nbsp;light and dark (white and blue) that denotes a split, foreshadowing Barry’s alienation and the rift between his state of mind and his (lack of) action. There is a degree of distortion in this shot (the background bends), which contributes to the rarified ambience of the scene and externalizes Barry's conflict: his reality is distorted due to past family trauma.</p>"
                                }
                            ],
                            "target": "https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00321/canvas/1#xywh=16,205,712,213"
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00321/canvas/1/74118241-1bbf-4498-9401-460657d9c928",
                            "type": "Annotation",
                            "motivation": "commenting",
                            "body": [
                                {
                                    "created": "2025-07-29T20:33:08.614Z",
                                    "creator": "Naveah",
                                    "purpose": "commenting",
                                    "type": "TextualBody",
                                    "format": "text/html",
                                    "value": "<p>Barry’s communication with others tends to be awkward and strained, marked by misunderstandings. In this case, he offers to provide his home phone number to a client, which speaks to his loneliness and inner desire to connect. Being too open on the phone will lead to trouble when he calls a phone sex line.</p><p>“Bye-bye”—the same thing he says to Lena after their first date and for which he quietly berates himself. Much like the film's key visual cues (colors foremost among them), words will recur throughout <i>Punch-Drunk Love</i>.</p>"
                                }
                            ],
                            "target": "https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00321/canvas/1#xywh=891,502,243,186"
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00321/canvas/1/aa9d37e0-0480-4604-b8b8-fc3e7540d872",
                            "type": "Annotation",
                            "motivation": "commenting",
                            "body": [
                                {
                                    "created": "2025-07-29T20:34:46.694Z",
                                    "creator": "Naveah",
                                    "purpose": "commenting",
                                    "type": "TextualBody",
                                    "format": "text/html",
                                    "value": "<p>Blue is a significant color throughout the film. In addition to an outward expression of his state of mind (his sadness or lack of fulfillment), it also serves to blend Barry to the background, perhaps indicating that there is a degree of inertness about him, like the wall against which this shot depicts him. His suit and tie are blue, though his tie will change colors throughout the film, as he gains agency though love.</p>"
                                }
                            ],
                            "target": "https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00321/canvas/1#xywh=1183,418,250,178"
                        }
                    ]
